---
import DocsLayout from "../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";

const breadcrumbs = [{ label: "Getting Started" }];
const headings = [
  { text: "With MCP", id: "mcp", depth: 2 },
  { text: "Manual (Copy & Paste)", id: "manual", depth: 2 },
  { text: "Prompt Templates", id: "prompts", depth: 2 },
  { text: "Foundation Overview", id: "foundation", depth: 2 },
];
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Getting Started"
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
  headings={headings}
  pudgePose="happytalk"
  pudgeMessage="Pick MCP for the fastest setup, or copy-paste if you prefer manual control."
>
  <h1>Getting Started</h1>
  <p>pudge-ui works by feeding design specs to your coding agent. There are two ways to use it.</p>

  <h2 id="mcp">With MCP (Recommended)</h2>
  <p>If your tool supports MCP (Claude Code, Cursor, etc.), add pudge-ui as an MCP server:</p>
  <pre><code>{`{
  "mcpServers": {
    "pudge-ui": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "pudge-ui-mcp"]
    }
  }
}`}</code></pre>
  <p>Then ask your agent:</p>
  <pre><code>"Build me a push button using pudge-ui specs"</code></pre>
  <p>The MCP server serves foundation context + component specs automatically.</p>

  <h2 id="manual">Manual (Copy & Paste)</h2>
  <p>No MCP? No problem. Copy the specs directly into your LLM context:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <strong>Copy foundation files</strong> — Start with
      <a href="/foundation/tokens">tokens</a>,
      <a href="/foundation/materials">materials</a>, and
      <a href="/foundation/depth">depth model</a>.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Copy component spec</strong> — Browse the <a href="/components">component gallery</a>,
      find the component you need, and use the "Copy spec for LLM" button.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Paste into your LLM</strong> — Include both foundation + component spec in your prompt.
    </li>
  </ol>

  <h2 id="prompts">Prompt Templates</h2>
  <p>
    For best results, use structured prompts. See the <a href="/for-llms">For LLMs guide</a> for templates
    and tips.
  </p>

  <h2 id="foundation">Foundation Overview</h2>
  <p>The foundation consists of 9 specification files that define the design system's rules:</p>
  <div class="table-scroll">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>File</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr
          ><td><a href="/foundation/tokens">tokens.md</a></td><td
            >Color, spacing, typography, radius, motion, shadow values</td
          ></tr
        >
        <tr
          ><td><a href="/foundation/materials">materials.md</a></td><td
            >6 material recipes with full CSS</td
          ></tr
        >
        <tr
          ><td><a href="/foundation/depth">depth-model.md</a></td><td
            >Shadow stack rules, press interactions, glow effects</td
          ></tr
        >
        <tr
          ><td><a href="/foundation/philosophy">philosophy.md</a></td><td>Core design principles</td
          ></tr
        >
        <tr><td><a href="/foundation/naming">naming.md</a></td><td>Class naming conventions</td></tr
        >
        <tr><td><a href="/foundation/layout">layout.md</a></td><td>Grid and spacing system</td></tr>
        <tr><td><a href="/foundation/theme">theme.md</a></td><td>Dark/light mode token sets</td></tr
        >
        <tr
          ><td><a href="/foundation/canvas">canvas.md</a></td><td
            >Canvas rendering specs for animated components</td
          ></tr
        >
        <tr
          ><td><a href="/foundation/accessibility">accessibility.md</a></td><td
            >ARIA patterns and keyboard navigation</td
          ></tr
        >
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
